Job description: Outsourcing/Accounting Manager
Outsourcing/Accounting Manager is responsible for reporting to Partner and will have direct responsibility as follows:
- Supervise the works of staffs in outsourcing/accounting department to assist them fulfill their assigned duty;
- Maintain good relationship with clients;
- Review report issued;
- Overall responsibility for accounting works ensuring that professional standards are adhered to;
- Lead and coach staffs in the outsourcing department: conduct training for accounting staff and update knowledge on tax regulations Accounting standards, etc.;
- Review staff performance;
- Keep up to date on all Vietnamese laws and regulations that relate to finance and accounting matters;
- Other tasks as required by Partner.

Job description: Accountant
Accountant – Outsourcing Department is responsible for reporting to Accounting Senior/Manager and will have direct responsibility as follows:
- Ensure accounting records are maintained in compliance with VAS;
- Perform all standard accounting duties and account for all expenditures;
- Maintain up-to-date and accurate financial records of a combined multi-transaction;
- Prepare in a timely manner all monthly financial information including monthly accounts, balance sheets and all schedules requested;
- Prepare reconciliation reports for Bank account and cost Inventory;
- Manufacture cost calculation and cost breakdown analysis;
- Keep up to date on all Vietnamese laws and regulations that relate to finance and accounting matters e.g. staff, office operations and other relevant issues and ensure that the company is informed of such matters;
- Monitor and support taxation issues;
- Other tasks as required by Senior/Manager.

